    [
      [
        "NO"
      ],
      [
        "[Paul], what the hell is wrong with you? You broke my control!"
      ],
      [
        "Shut up, Shut up! You had to be a bitch and win, right?"
      ],
      [
        "Do you think you’re better than me?"
      ],
      [
        "[Paul], get out of my house. NOW. "
      ],
      [
        "[Paul] takes a step towards me with clenched fists, "
      ],
      [
        "but I swiftly pull a taser I had stored away in my drawer."
      ],
      [
        "It actually didn’t work, but [Paul] doesn’t have to know that. "
      ],
      [
        "I stand up, trying not to think about how much my leg hurts. "
      ],
      [
        "[Paul], get out. I’m not joking about this. "
      ],
      [
        "Ha! taking that taser out of your hands will be easy when you have that useless leg."
      ],
      [
        "Yeah? and then what? you’re gonna beat me up?"
      ],
      [
        "If you do, just know that Helpie will come home eventually,"
      ],
      [
        "and If they find me unconscious or don’t even find me here, the police will be called."
      ],
      [
        "Who do you think will be the main suspect when there was only one person with me in the night?"
      ],
      [
        "[Paul] took a step back and looked aside, as if [his] logic was being defeated."
      ],
      [
        "He glared at me but decided to turn and walk away. "
      ],
      [
        "Screw you!"
      ],
      [
        "That’s the last thing I hear before my front door is slammed."
      ],
      [
        "I exhale and go to make sure all doors and windows are locked."
      ],
      [
        "After that, I exhale and sit on my bed."
      ],
      [
        "My leg is killing me as my adrenaline dies down and I relax. "
      ],
      [
        "I look at the hour and it's 1:00 AM."
      ],
      [
        "It’s gonna be a long wait until Helpie comes home, but I really don’t want to sleep anyways."
      ],
      [
        "I lay down and look at my ceiling."
      ],
      [
        "After all, I’m glad things turned out this way. "
      ],
      [
        "Because now I realize how bad [Paul] was for me."
      ],
      [
        "I don’t plan on seeing [him] ever again."
      ]
    ],
